ONE:
compare Typescript/NX w/  gradle/JVM builds:

    Me 

         I would say a JVM base build with about the same amount of tests and production code would be substantially longer, how much longer do you think?
    
    AI demon

        Probably 5-15x longer — so 5 to 15 minutes for a comparable JVM project. The big drivers:

        - JVM startup + compilation adds 30-60s before a single test runs
        - Gradle/Maven dependency resolution can add another 30-60s on a cold cache
        - TypeScript tsc is dramatically faster than javac / kotlinc for equivalent LOC



